text: Jefferson Davis County is a county located in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 11,321 people lived there. Its county seat is Prentiss. The county was founded on March 31, 1906. It is named in honor of Mississippi Senator and Confederate President Jefferson Davis. == References == == Other websites == * Official county website Category:1900s establishments in Mississippi Category:1906 establishments in the United States Category:Mississippi counties
